
[1]illusion

   ILLU'SION, n. s as z. [L. illusio, from illudo, to illude.] Deceptive
   appearance; false show, by which a person is or may be deceived, or his
   expectations disappointed; mockery.

   Ye soft illusions, dear deceits, arise!
